\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Pollution and greenhouse gas emissions have fallen across continents as countries try to contain the spread of the new coronavirus. Is this just a fleeting change, or could it lead to longer-lasting falls in emissions? \
I\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf2 In a matter of months, the world has been transformed. Thousands of people have already died, and hundreds of thousands more have fallen ill, from a coronavirus that was previously unknown before appearing in the city of Wuhan in December 2019. For millions of others who have not caught the disease, their entire way of life has changed by it.\
The streets of Wuhan, China, are deserted after authorities implemented a strict lockdown. In Italy, the most {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-51737226"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 extensive travel restrictions}} are in place since World War Two. In London, the normally bustling {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/explainers-52010555"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 pubs, bars and theatres have been closed}} and people have been told to stay in their homes. Worldwide, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.bbc.com/news/business-51904769"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 flights are being cancelled}} or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51887707"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 turning around in mid-air}}, as the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.bbc.com/news/business-51893151"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 aviation industry buckles}}. Those who are able to do so are holed up at home, practicing social distancing and working remotely.\
It is all aimed at controlling the spread of Covid-19, and hopefully reducing the death toll. But all this change has also led to some unexpected consequences. As industries, transport networks and businesses have closed down, it has brought a sudden drop in carbon emissions. Compared with this time last year, levels of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-51944780"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 pollution in New York have reduced by nearly 50% because of measures to contain the virus}}.\
